    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but you're kind of picking and choosing which nationalism is \"good\" based on whether it fits a certain globalist mold. you called Sweden and Canada models, but those are very specific, liberal democracies. what about people who feel that strong, traditional national identity is the only thing protecting their culture from being erased? are you saying their view is inherently \"toxic\" just because it doesn't look like the Swedish model?",
